{{Youmay|the starfighter pilot|[[David Wessman]], nicknamed "Wotan"}}
'''Wotan''' developed the [[Corkscrew Avoid|Wotan Weave]], a maneuver used by [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] to avoid enemy fire.

==Behind the scenes==
Wotan was first mentioned in the glossary of ''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]'', a guide to the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] [[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']], written by [[Rusel DeMaria]], [[David Maxwell]] and [[David Wessman]]<ref name="XWOSG">''[[X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide]]''</ref> and published in [[June]] [[1993]].<ref name="Cargo Bay">{{CargoBay|url=item-detail/46|text=X-Wing: The Official Strategy Guide}}</ref> Wotan is the nickname of Wessman, who devised many of the strategies covered in the book.<ref name="XWOSG" />

